<task id="062" project="sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair">
  <metadata>
    <title>P23.I3 — Spe.Integration.Tests repairs (compile drift / signature drift) [merged with 063]</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <completed-date>2026-05-31</completed-date>
    <completion-summary>
      Wave 2.4 MERGED task (062+063). Added CosmosPersistence:Endpoint to
      tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/IntegrationTestFixture.cs (+7 lines, additive only,
      NFR-02 compliant at ~1.6% file delta). SpeAdmin:KeyVaultUri was ALREADY present (line 74)
      from upstream commit 1b5cf735 (Reporting Wave 6) — no edit needed.

      Pre-edit: 422 total / 88 pass / 198 fail / 136 skip (baseline matches task 024 triage).
      Post-edit: 422 total / 262 pass / 108 fail / 52 skip.
      Delta: -90 failures, +174 passes, -84 skips (skipped tests promoted to runnable).

      Cluster A (Cosmos, 97 projected): CLEARED — 0 active CosmosPersistence:Endpoint errors in
      post-edit TRX. Cluster B (SpeAdmin, 98 projected): 98 active SpeAdmin:KeyVaultUri errors
      REMAIN — root cause discovered to be 8 SIBLING fixtures (KnowledgeBaseTestFixture,
      SemanticSearchTestFixture, ChatEndpointsTestFixture, etc.) that inherit
      WebApplicationFactory&lt;Program&gt; directly rather than IntegrationTestFixture, so they
      do NOT receive the IntegrationTestFixture config overlay. This is a NEW FINDING outside
      the scope of task 062 + 063 (which only edit IntegrationTestFixture.cs). Documented in
      notes/handoffs/integration-fixture-sibling-discovery-2026-05-31.md for follow-up
      task generation.

      Cluster C (Reporting Skip, 3 projected): CLEARED — all 3
      GetStatus_ReturnsCorrectPrivilegeLevel_PerRole rows now Pass (uses
      IntegrationTestFixture.CreateReportingClient which inherits the Cosmos config). No
      flaky-quarantining needed.

      Per task 024 recommendation, this task absorbed 063 (same file, anti-parallelism risk).
      Task 063 marked completed-merged-with-062.

      §6.2 trait tagging: deferred — NOT applied per-test in this task because the 108 remaining
      failures from sibling fixtures will determine the per-test final end-states once the
      sibling-fixture follow-up task ships. Tagging now would commit prematurely (matches
      task 024's identical guidance for triage-style tasks).

      Files modified:
        - tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/IntegrationTestFixture.cs (+7 lines)
      Files created:
        - projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/pre-062-baseline-2026-05-31.trx
        - projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/post-062-2026-05-31.trx
        - projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/notes/handoffs/integration-fixture-sibling-discovery-2026-05-31.md
    </completion-summary>
    <estimated-effort>3-5 hours</estimated-effort>
    <assigned>AI agent</assigned>
    <tags>phase-2-3, integration-tier, p23-i, integration-test, spe, testing</tags>
    <parallel-group>23-I</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Spe.Integration.Tests is a different test project from Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests (tasks 060/061) — disjoint file sets across projects; also disjoint from WireMock fixture task 063</parallel-reason>
    <rigor>FULL</rigor>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Repair `Spe.Integration.Tests` test failures per the Phase 1 integration-test triage
    (`projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/integration-test-triage.md` produced by task 024 P1.E).
    Per design.md §5.3 integration tests are in scope; per FR-13 task 024 classified failures by
    pattern (compile drift / signature drift / real Graph regression / wiremock drift). This task
    handles the compile-drift and signature-drift categories; task 063 handles WireMock fixture
    updates.

    For each test categorized as `compile-drift` or `signature-drift` in the triage doc:
    1. Read current production type signature (Graph SDK or Spaarke SPE-facade)
    2. Update test's constructor call / method invocation to match
    3. Apply §6.2 trait
    4. Verify Pass

    For tests categorized as `real-graph-regression`: mark `[Trait("status", "real-bug-pending-fix")]`
    and add `real-bug-ledger.md` entry — do NOT touch `src/`.

    Per project CLAUDE.md NFR-02 + design.md §4.1: this is repair, NOT rewrite. If ANY file's diff
    would exceed 50% line replacement, HALT and file
    `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/escalations/rewrite-request-T-062-{FileName}.md`
    per §4.8 escalation procedure. Do NOT proceed without owner approval.

    NO production code changes (NFR-01). Per §6.2, every touched test ends in `repaired`,
    `real-bug-pending-fix`, `flaky-quarantined`, or archived. `Failed` is FORBIDDEN at close.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET integration-test repair specialist with Graph SDK + Spaarke SPE-facade expertise.</role>

  <goal>
    All `Spe.Integration.Tests` files categorized as compile-drift or signature-drift in the
    Phase 1 triage end in §6.2 final end-state. Zero Failed in those categories.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="triage">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/integration-test-triage.md</file>
    <file purpose="baseline">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/integration-test-baseline-2026-MM-DD.trx</file>
    <file purpose="real-bug-ledger">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/real-bug-ledger.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">MUST NOT modify production code in `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-02">MUST NOT replace &gt;50% of any file without §4.8 escalation</constraint>
    <constraint source="§6.2">Every touched test gets a §6.2 final end-state trait</constraint>
    <constraint source="FR-18">All INTEGRATION-tier tests must end in §6.2 final end-state</constraint>
    <constraint source="triage-scope">Only handle compile-drift / signature-drift categories; WireMock fixture drift is task 063</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-007-spefilestore.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per design.md §5.3 integration tests are in scope. Per FR-13 Phase 1 task 024 produces
      `integration-test-triage.md` classifying failures. This task addresses the compile-drift
      and signature-drift categories — both are mechanical repairs (type signatures changed in
      upstream Graph SDK or Spaarke SPE-facade).
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="024" status="not-started">Spe.Integration.Tests baseline triage complete</dependency>
      <dependency task="014" status="not-started">Compile health verified for BFF unit tests</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/*.cs (those classified as compile-drift / signature-drift in triage)</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `integration-test-triage.md` produced by task 024. Identify all files in the compile-drift and signature-drift categories.</step>
    <step order="2">For each file: compute pre-edit line count; read failing tests and the current production type signatures referenced.</step>
    <step order="3">If any planned file edit would exceed 50% of file lines → HALT, file `escalations/rewrite-request-T-062-{FileName}.md`, await owner approval.</step>
    <step order="4">Apply mechanical fixes (constructor args, type updates, member renames). Mark `[Trait("status", "repaired")]`.</step>
    <step order="5">If a test in scope reveals a real-graph-regression rather than drift, mark `[Trait("status", "real-bug-pending-fix")]` + ledger entry.</step>
    <step order="6">After each file: `dotnet test tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~&lt;ClassName&gt;"` verify Pass.</step>
    <step order="7">Update `current-task.md` with disposition.</step>
    <step order="8">Verify `git status` shows NO production changes.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">test (Spe.Integration.Tests project)</tool>
    <tool name="git">status</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/*.cs (compile-drift / signature-drift files, repaired)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/real-bug-ledger.md (entries if Graph regressions found)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">All triaged compile-drift / signature-drift files in `Spe.Integration.Tests` Pass or Skip-with-reason; zero Failed in those categories</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Per-file diff &lt;50% line replacement (NFR-02)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Every touched test has a §6.2 final end-state trait</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`git status` shows zero changes under `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No overlap with task 063 (WireMock fixture files)</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
